key_deliverables: Federated BIM Model (LOD 300): A coordinated model combining all disciplines to resolve clashes and finalize spatial allocations, which is critical before committing to off-site modular manufacturing.
Architectural Model (LOD 300): Detailing the building mass, modular panel breaks, apartment layouts, core, commercial space, window/door locations, and integrated private balconies.
Structural Model (LOD 300): Defining the primary modular frame (steel or timber), pile foundation strategy, and central circulation core, with accurate geometry for coordination.
MEP Model (LOD 300): Showing main plant equipment (Smart HVAC, rainwater harvesting), primary service routes, riser locations, and defined service penetration zones for pre-manufacturing sign-off.
Site Plan & Logistics Plan: 2D drawing showing building footprint, site context, utility application points, and a preliminary plan for modular unit delivery, storage, and craning.

General Arrangement Floor Plans (2D): Drawings for Ground Floor (commercial, lobby, services), Typical Upper Floor (1/2-bed mix, double-loaded corridor), and Roof Level (green roof, solar array layout).
Building Elevations and Key Sections (2D): Illustrating the external appearance, materiality, and vertical arrangement of spaces, including floor-to-floor heights and facade system integration.
Typical Modular Unit Drawings (2D): Standardized plans, sections, and elevations for the 1-bed and 2-bed modules, forming the basis for off-site manufacturing.
Geotechnical Investigation Report: A mandatory report detailing ground conditions to inform the pile foundation design.

Outline Specification Document: A consolidated document defining performance criteria for architectural systems (facades, roofing), structural systems (modular frame choice), and MEP systems (plant, acoustic performance, sustainability features like solar PV).
Energy & Sustainability Statement: Report demonstrating compliance with the London Plan's 'Be Lean, Be Clean, Be Green' hierarchy and detailing the strategy for the green roof and solar array.
Acoustic Strategy Report: A detailed report addressing noise from plant, service transmission, and compartment separation in the high-density urban context.

details: BIM/CAD documentation plan, refined 3D render, and simulated 3D plan generated.
